title: For Sale:  Kifaru Highcamp 7000ci and 24” Bikini Frame w/ warranty and receipt.
postcontent: Kifaru Highcamp 7000ci and 24” Bikini Frame w/ warranty and receipt. Pictures seen here: http://kalispell.craigslist.org/spo/REDACTED.htmlAbsolutely excellent condition Kifaru backpack. I purchased the pack less than 2 years ago for $662, but recently adopted a 2 year old and became a dad, so I need to sell my overnight gear. You’ll receive everything that came with the frame and bag. They have not been modified at all. I’ll also provide the receipt (attached) so you can be covered by the Kifaru warranty. I could not find any signs of wear to photograph. I’m keeping the separately purchased accessories for my day pack. I’m not ready to give up hunting altogether. I don’t want to discourage you from using the Highcamp as a daypack, however. The Highcamp was originally my daypack in case I knocked an elk down, and it worked great because it cinches down so small but can expand, but I’ll have to settle for something else.I’m an ultralight hunter and this was definitely pack of choice. The frame weighs 38oz. The bag weighs 32oz. Both have incredible versatility and modularity, and can handle a lot weight, comfortably. This is by far the best pack I have ever owned. It isn’t even in the same league as the Eberlestock and Badlands packs I’ve owned. If you do enough research and talk to enough people, you’ll find it universally accepted that Kifaru packs outshine the other top tier packs as well, such as Mystery Ranch, Kuiu, etc. You just cannot beat the comfort and load bearing capacity of Kifaru. If you’re on the fence about which brand to go with, I’d spend some time on rokslide.com and read reviews. You’ll find quickly that many of the members, especially the admin and senior staff, are dedicated hikers and outdoorsman and know what they’re talking about. They always try to be neutral between brands, but, as you’ll see, almost all of them give kifaru packs the advantage. This universal approval is what drove me to buy kifaru, and I was not disappointed in the slightest. Outside of rokslide, if you are talking with someone who has tried a variety of packs, you’ll find that almost all of them swear by Kifaru.A good place to start for reviews would be here: http://www.rokslide.com/forums/showthread.php?5249-Kifaru-Mystery-Ranch-KUIU-BadlandsRokslide member Bitteroot Bulls did an extensive and unbiased comparison on some of the top of the line packs, and, in the end, admitted that Kifaru edged out the competition. The comparison test thread: http://www.rokslide.com/forums/showthread.php?4375-Stone-Glacier-and-Kifaru/page11View the tutorial video on the bag here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1f-0GdroMVcTech specs on Highcamp:7,000ci/114 liter main bag 45”/114cm upper circumference36”/91cm lower circumference seam to seam 13”/33cm lower width 10”/25cm depth 33.5”/85cm tall 7.5”/19cm x 14.5”/36cm lower access panel openingPositive seller history: http://feedback.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewFeedback2&userid=mt_outdoorsman
